    <item>
      <title>Submit to an appropriate journal</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/submit-to-an-appropriate-journal/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 20:14:41 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/submit-to-an-appropriate-journal/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/zh/submit-to-an-appropriate-journal.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/submit-to-an-appropriate-journal/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/submit-to-an-appropriate-journal/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/submit-to-an-appropriate-journal/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;submit-to-an-appropriate-journal&#34;&gt;Submit to an appropriate journal&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Few, but ripe.&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href=&#34;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Friedrich_Gauss&#34;&gt;Carl Friedrich Gauss&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It is always tempting to submit a paper to a prestigious journal, but if the paper makes only a borderline case for publication in this journal, then the net result may be a lengthy process, critical reviews holding the paper to a very high standard, and ultimate rejection of the paper.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Use the introduction to “sell” the key points of your paper</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/use-the-introduction-to-sell-the-key-points-of-your-paper/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 20:13:57 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/use-the-introduction-to-sell-the-key-points-of-your-paper/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/zh/use-the-introduction-to-sell-the-key-points-of-your-paper.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/use-the-introduction-to-%E2%80%9Csell%E2%80%9D-the-key-points-of-your-paper/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/use-the-introduction-to-%E2%80%9Csell%E2%80%9D-the-key-points-of-your-paper/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/use-the-introduction-to-%E2%80%9Csell%E2%80%9D-the-key-points-of-your-paper/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;use-the-introduction-to-sell-the-key-points-of-your-paper&#34;&gt;Use the introduction to &amp;ldquo;sell&amp;rdquo; the key points of your paper&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A rule to live by: I won&amp;rsquo;t use anything I can&amp;rsquo;t explain in five minutes.&#xA;— Philip Crosby&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Every now and then as editor, I see an author upset at a rejection of a paper because the referee &amp;ldquo;clearly did not grasp the key point of the paper&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Submit a final draft, not a first draft</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/submit-a-final-draft-not-a-first-draft/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 20:13:18 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/submit-a-final-draft-not-a-first-draft/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/zh/submit-a-final-draft-not-a-first-draft.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/submit-a-final-draft-not-a-first-draft/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/submit-a-final-draft-not-a-first-draft/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/submit-a-final-draft-not-a-first-draft/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;submit-a-final-draft-not-a-first-draft&#34;&gt;Submit a final draft, not a first draft&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s not at all important to get it right the first time. It&amp;rsquo;s vitally important to get it right the last time.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;— Andrew Hunt and David Thomas, &amp;ldquo;The pragmatic programmer&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This is a corollary to &amp;ldquo;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/proofread-and-double-check-your-paper-before-submission/&#34;&gt;Proofread and double-check your paper before submission&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>On our duties as scientists</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/on-our-duties-as-scientists/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/on-our-duties-as-scientists/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/on-our-duties-as-scientists.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;http://www.wisdom.weizmann.ac.il/%7Eoded/on-duties.html&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;http://www.wisdom.weizmann.ac.il/%7Eoded/on-duties.html&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    http://www.wisdom.weizmann.ac.il/%7Eoded/on-duties.html&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;on-our-duties-as-scientists&#34;&gt;On our duties as scientists&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Our primary duty as scientists is to contribute to the progress of science.&#xA;By doing so, we best fulfill our duties to the society at large.&#xA;Our primary duty is not fulfilled by merely doing research,&#xA;but rather by communicating our findings to the relevant scientific community.&#xA;The key role of this community in the scientific process,&#xA;entails some important (secondary) duties&#xA;towards this community (e.g., evaluation of scientific work&#xA;and education of future generations of researchers).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
